# Documentation (KDoc / comments) — mandatory

## Language
- **English only** for KDoc/README/public API comments. Never write documentation in other languages.

## KDoc links
- **Forbidden:** fully qualified names in link targets (no `[Foo][full.package.Foo]`).
- **Required:** use only simple names that resolve via imports: `[Foo]`, `[SomeType.member]`.
- Every referenced type/member in KDoc links must be importable and imported in the same file.
- If a target is in another module and cannot be imported, use **plain text** (no link).

## Scope rules
- In `object` / class-level KDoc, do **not** link to function parameters by name (out of scope). Use plain text and move parameter links to function-level KDoc.
- When documentation is requested for a **package**, the scope includes all subpackages.

## Comments
- Use inline comments sparingly; do not narrate obvious behavior.
- Prefer clear naming and KDoc for public surface; comment only when intent/constraints are non-obvious.
